title: ChoiceCard_M2_OptionA_Erase
tags: choice_card mission2 option_a erase
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Mission 2 — Moral Choice Card option previews.
// Author: Esme Cordray (Choice & Consequence Architect)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/02_THE_WIDOWER_GERROLD.md § 5
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_2.md § 14
//
// The Cordray Principle § 9: "The player infers the consequence; they are
// never given numbers." All four option previews are written in fiction-
// voice. No stat bars. No moral-alignment indicator. Just four sentences
// and the orb in the player's hand.
//
// ChoiceCardUI consumes these node titles for the four option previews.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ChoiceLabel: A — Erase the long bit.
ChoicePreview: He will remember he loved her.
ChoicePreview: He will not remember the dying.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_OptionB_Cleanse
tags: choice_card mission2 option_b cleanse canonical
---
ChoiceLabel: B — Cleanse with care.
ChoicePreview: He will keep the memory, gentler.
ChoicePreview: You will need a careful hand.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_OptionC_Listen
tags: choice_card mission2 option_c listen vow7
---
ChoiceLabel: C — Don't take the memory. Sit with him.
ChoicePreview: He will carry it.
ChoicePreview: You will have only been here.
ChoicePreview: Sometimes that is enough.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_OptionD_Defer
tags: choice_card mission2 option_d defer
---
ChoiceLabel: D — Ask him to come back tomorrow.
ChoicePreview: He will.
ChoicePreview: You can think about this for a day.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_Setup
tags: choice_card mission2 setup framing
---
// The framing text at the top of the choice card UI.
// Per Mission 2 Guide § 14.1.

ChoiceFraming: Gerrold has placed the orb on the table.
ChoiceFraming: He is waiting.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_EraseConfirm
tags: choice_card mission2 option_a confirm
---
// Second-confirmation prompt that appears when player chooses Option A
// (Erase) per Mission 2 Guide § 14.4. The HEAVIEST option requires a
// second yes. Cancel returns to the main 4-option choice card.

ChoiceConfirm: Yes, all of it. Erase the long bit.
ChoiceCancel: Wait — let me think a moment more.

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_ListenSubChoice
tags: choice_card mission2 option_c sub_choice
---
// The Listen path's TWO sub-options per Focus 02 § 5.1 + Gerrold_M2_ChoiceListen.
// Both end at Mission2_ListenScene_FullMonologue, but the gestural option
// grants Vow 7 +7 (vs +5 for verbal) and Cinder +3 (vs +2).

ChoiceLabel_Verbal: I want to listen. Tell me about it. Hold it the whole time. I won't take it.
ChoiceLabel_Gestural: (Reach out and gently place his hands around the orb.)

===

title: ChoiceCard_M2_ChairSelection
tags: choice_card mission2 cottage chair
---
// The cottage chair-selection sub-choice. Per Gerrold_M2_CottageInterior.
// "Sit in Margery's chair" enables Pickle's M2_MargerysChair line if
// pickle_approval >= 50.

ChoiceLabel_LeftChair: (Sit in the left chair — Gerrold's chair.)
ChoiceLabel_RightChair: (Sit in the right chair — Margery's chair.)
ChoiceLabel_Fireplace: (Stand by the fireplace.)

===

title: ChoiceCard_M1_PriceNegotiation
tags: choice_card mission1 doris price
---
// Mission 1 — Doris price-negotiation card. Per Doris_M1_PriceNegotiation.
// Three options. No second-confirm needed (the heaviest is overpay, which
// Doris herself softens to settle at 5 cu instead of accepting 6).

ChoiceFraming_M1: Doris has set her price.
ChoiceFraming_M1: Four coppers, plain. She will not let you ruin yourself.

ChoiceLabel_Honor: Four coppers is fair.
ChoicePreview_Honor: (Honor the price.)

ChoiceLabel_Overpay: I'll pay six.
ChoicePreview_Overpay: (She will not let you overpay. She'll settle at five.)

ChoiceLabel_Underpay: Two coppers. That's all I have.
ChoicePreview_Underpay: (You will owe her. She will not mention it again. You will.)

===

title: HeavyThemeCard_M2_Cottage
tags: heavy_theme_card mission2 cottage warning
---
// Heavy Theme Warning Card — fires before the Mission 2 cottage scene
// IF the player has the warning toggle ON (default ON).
// Per Mission 2 Guide § 13.2 + Codex 06 (Tone Compass).

HeavyTheme_Header: This scene contains references to:
HeavyTheme_Body:
HeavyTheme_Body: — Loss of spouse
HeavyTheme_Body: — Terminal illness (referenced)
HeavyTheme_Body: — A man's grief
HeavyTheme_Body:
HeavyTheme_Body: Take a breath if you need to.
HeavyTheme_Body: The cat is still on the windowsill back at the shop.
HeavyTheme_Dismiss: [ Dismiss ]

===

title: TeaBrewing_LavenderResolveChord
tags: tea_brewing mission2 lavender audio_cue
---
// Tea-brewing pour-cue narrative metadata. Per Focus 06 § 3.2 +
// Mission 2 Guide § 11.3.
// A 3-second composer-mixed micro-cue: kettle pour sound + a single
// sustained note that resolves into a soft C major chord.
// Audio system (SfxLibrarySO) plays the actual stems — this Yarn node
// documents the narrative intent for the composer.

TeaResolveChord: Lavender resolves into C major.
TeaResolveChord: The cozy player will register this as warmth without
TeaResolveChord: consciously identifying why.

===

title: TeaBrewing_ValerianResolveChord
tags: tea_brewing mission2 valerian audio_cue
---
TeaResolveChord: Valerian resolves into D minor.
TeaResolveChord: The cozy player will register this as unease without
TeaResolveChord: consciously identifying why. Pickle does not approve.

===
